================================================================================
Third-party components
================================================================================

citelock's core (the `citelock` package excluding the optional `[nli]` and
`[llm]` extras) depends only on the following, installed from PyPI and NOT
redistributed in this repository:

  - pydantic            MIT License
  - syntok              MIT License
  - python-ulid         MIT License
  - blake3              CC0-1.0 / Apache-2.0 (dual)   [hash-chain; see ledger.py]

Optional extras (installed only when requested, NOT part of the core install):

  [nli]
  - torch               BSD-3-Clause
  - transformers        Apache-2.0
  - sentencepiece       Apache-2.0

Default NLI model (downloaded at runtime from the Hugging Face Hub, NOT
redistributed here):

  - cross-encoder/nli-deberta-v3-base     Apache-2.0
        Trained on SNLI + MultiNLI (both research/commercial-permissive).

Opt-in NLI models (the user must select these explicitly; citelock prints a
license warning before use and never selects them by default):

  - MoritzLaurer/DeBERTa-v3-base-mnli-fever-anli   MIT (model weights)
        NOTE: its training data includes ANLI (CC-BY-NC-4.0). Use under the
        terms applicable to your deployment.
  - lytang/MiniCheck-DeBERTa-v3-Large              CC-BY-NC-4.0 (NON-commercial)

================================================================================
Design lineage
================================================================================

citelock reuses the *design ideas* (fail-closed gating, append-only per-item
ledger) of the author's earlier project `subjunctor`. subjunctor is MIT-licensed
TypeScript; NO subjunctor source code is copied into citelock.

